import bs4
import requests
import json

def scraper(url: str) -> str:
  # get html from url
  response = requests.get(url)
  soup = bs4.BeautifulSoup(response.text, "html.parser")

  # find all question summaries
  question_summaries = soup.find_all("div", class_="question-summary")

  # create list to store data
  top_questions = []

  for summary in question_summaries:
    # extract question title
    question_title = summary.find("a", class_="question-hyperlink").text

    # extract tags
    tags = []
    tag_list = summary.find("div", class_="tags").find_all("a")
    for tag in tag_list:
      tags.append(tag.text)

    # extract username from question stats

    # create dictionary with data

      "question_title" : question_title,
      "tags" : tags,
      "user_name" : user_name
    }

    # add dictionary to list
    top_questions.append(question_data)

  # convert list to json and print
  print(json.dumps(top_questions))

if __name__ == '__main__':
  url = "https://math.stackexchange.com/questions"
